Gerda Steyn’s success comes less than five years after she began serious road running. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - It’s almost two weeks since a bubbly Gerda Steyn produced a record-breaking Comrades Marathon win. Steyn’s success comes less than five years after she began serious road running in December 2014. The Free State-born 29-year-old joined a running club during a work-related stint in Dubai, as a way to make friends hasn’t looked back since then. READ: Paralympic dreams for young athlete Steyn is spending the next few weeks in recovery from the Comrades Marathon. The ever-smiling athletics sensation won’t confirm her next major race just yet but could look to qualify for the Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games. eNCA reporter Hloni Mtimkulu caught up with Steyn, watch the video above.